## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 3 (affecting all 10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 1 |
| **Low** | 0 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. All 10 public methods of `ProductCatalog` are invoked — producing 95% line coverage — but **zero tests verify actual behavior**. Every test will pass even if the production code is completely wrong.

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (systematic) — all 10 tests

The test class methodically calls every public method on `ProductCatalog` with either no assertion or only a trivial `Assert.IsNotNull`. The tests follow declaration order of the production API. This is the canonical coverage-inflation pattern and the direct explanation for "95% coverage, bugs in production."

#### 2. No Assertions — 6 of 10 tests

These tests execute production code and discard the result. They can never fail regardless of how broken the implementation is.

| Test Method | Line | What it misses |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 17–21 | Never verifies the product was persisted |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 31–36 | Never verifies the price actually changed |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 38–43 | Never verifies the product was deleted |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 62–66 | Never checks the returned count value |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 68–74 | Never checks that prices were reduced |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 84–88 | Never verifies the product was imported |

**Example fix — `UpdatePrice_Works`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE (line 31-36): passes even if UpdatePrice is a no-op
public void UpdatePrice_Works()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);
}

// AFTER: verifies the observable outcome
[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ExistingProduct_PriceIsUpdated()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated!.Price);
}
```

**Example fix — `RemoveProduct_Works`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE (line 38-43): passes even if RemoveProduct does nothing
// AFTER:
[TestMethod]
public void RemoveProduct_ExistingProduct_ProductIsNoLongerFound()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));

    _catalog.RemoveProduct("SKU-001");

    Assert.IsNull(_catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001"));
}
```

**Example fix — `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works`:**

```csharp
// BEFORE (line 68-74): passes even if discount math is inverted
// AFTER:
[TestMethod]
public void ApplyBulkDiscount_TenPercent_ReducesPricesByTenPercent()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 100.00m));

    _catalog.ApplyBulkDiscount(0.10m);

    var product = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(90.00m, product!.Price);
